<BR><A HREF="http://www.krunch.net/spiritslammer">Clan Spiritslammer</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoricthemad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric the Mad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brell's man of Nomex</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/15/01 3:41:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/BrianPic_copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ponder, Reservation for Fear and Hate...</span><hr size=1> There's actually nothing to keep a guild that wants to do inny or cazic from coordinating to take them on after an armor raid by another guild either. In the case of the new hate especially, most people wont even be venturing into the second floor at all. You could easily have a 50'ish armor raid going on on the first floor and sneak a mage up to a ss on the second floor to coh a high level raid to mess around up there at the same time. Other than lag concerns they wouldnt even interact with one another.  <p>ICQ#-105127301<BR>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/ThoricPSD3_copy.gif"></A> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualvimar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alvimar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/15/01 3:46:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ponder, Reservation for Fear and Hate...</span><hr size=1> Unless something unforseen happens like odd agros... Seems a bit early on to be talking about 2 raids up there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 572<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/15/01 3:59:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ponder, Reservation for Fear and Hate...</span><hr size=1> Maybe not at the same time but I wouldn't see why you couldn't have a raid on Saturday or Sunday afternoon and then allow a higher level raid to head in afterwards that evening that wanted to head up to the 2nd floor.  They could get to the 2nd floor without bothering the 1st floor mobs other than the armorless roamers.  Same with Fear.  I would bet that most guilds will clear the plane other than CT, Draco and maybe a golem or two.  Once they finished up a high level raid could move in and clear up the rest.  <br>
<br>
No armor would go to waste.<br>
The smaller raids still get to raid the plane.<br>
The higher level raids would get a shot at the gods.<br>
Killing the gods would make the next 6 days of raiding much easier.<br>
<br>
As long as people TALK to each other I don't see why this wouldn't work.  I certainly wouldn't have a problem if after my raid that SR, LoH, Enshadowed, etc wanted to head in to take down the god.  Of course it would also be nice to make sure that SR, LoH, Enshadowed etc doesn't have the plane the next day or so.  But I don't see this being too much of a problem at least until more than just a small handful of guilds have the ability to take them down.   Eventually they will drop regularly again.<br>
