</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukyanamysteblayde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyana Mysteblayde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/16/01 9:58:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ponder, Reservation for Fear and Hate...</span><hr size=1> I don't think leaving a day open would really help get the Gods killed. Say Tuesday was the day left open.  What happens if the God dies on Monday.  Then you just have a Tuesday with no raid or people fighting over who gets to do the impromptu raid.  I wouldn't have a problem seeing someone go in and kill the Gods after an armor raid was over.  I agree the key issue is communication and timing.  In a perfect setting, the armor raid leader and the God raid leader talk and have everything settled before the armor raid starts.  When the armor raid is over, the leader sends a tell to the God raid leader.  They go in and kill the God.   Worst case scenario is the God raid leader waits until 15 minutes before the armor raid leader starts their raid, wanting to discuss it. Constant tells asking if the armor raid is over. God raiders start heading in early and screw up the armor raid.  <br>
<br>
Just from what I've read about the attempts on the Gods so far, going LD seems to be a problem.  I am wondering if having 2 raids going at the same time would just wipe out both raids.  Also, do the God's then become claimable? Do you have to sign up as a &quot;second Fear raid&quot; or &quot;second Hate raid&quot; on the boards, and if the God happens to be up you get him, if not you just picked the wrong day?  I am honestly all for the Gods going down as soon as possible. I also would have no problem with others coming in after a raid and killing the God, if the raid I was on couldn't. I don't see a problem with the idea of a second raid to kill the Gods. I do forsee lots of problems with communication.<br>
